==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fng-hwang
<hw>F⟦ecir⟧ng"-hwang`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin.
<ets>feng</ets> + <ets>⟦lsquo⟧huang</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chinese
Myth.)</fld> <def>A pheasantlike bird of rich plumage and graceful form
and movement, fabled to appear in the land on the accession of a sage to
the throne, or when right principles are about to prevail. It is often
represented on porcelains and other works of art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

